Requests for grants and subsidies shall be submitted to the appropriate standing committees of the legislature at the start of each regular session of the legislature.  Each request shall state:



	(1)	The name of the requesting organization;
	(2)	The public purpose for the grant or subsidy;
	(3)	The services to be supported by the grant or subsidy;
	(4)	The target group; and
	(5)	The cost of the grant or subsidy and the budget. [L 1997, c 190, pt of §3]
